## Semantic Tokens (Use These in Code)

### Background Colors
```css
--bg-default: var(--color-gray-50);        /* Page background */
--bg-surface: white;                       /* Card, modal background */
--bg-subtle: var(--color-gray-100);       /* Hover states */
--bg-muted: var(--color-gray-200);        /* Disabled states */

--bg-primary: var(--color-primary-500);   /* Primary buttons */
--bg-primary-hover: var(--color-primary-600);

--bg-success: var(--color-success-50);    /* Success backgrounds */
--bg-error: var(--color-error-50);        /* Error backgrounds */
--bg-warning: var(--color-warning-50);    /* Warning backgrounds */
--bg-info: var(--color-info-50);          /* Info backgrounds */
```

### Text Colors
```css
--text-default: var(--color-gray-900);    /* Body text */
--text-subtle: var(--color-gray-600);     /* Secondary text */
--text-muted: var(--color-gray-500);      /* Placeholder text */
--text-inverse: white;                     /* Text on dark backgrounds */

--text-primary: var(--color-primary-600);
--text-success: var(--color-success-700);
--text-error: var(--color-error-700);
--text-warning: var(--color-warning-700);
```

### Border Colors
```css
--border-default: var(--color-gray-300);
--border-subtle: var(--color-gray-200);
--border-focus: var(--color-primary-500);
--border-error: var(--color-error-500);
--border-success: var(--color-success-500);
```

## Accessibility Standards

### Contrast Ratios (WCAG 2.1)
- **Normal text (< 18px)**: 4.5:1 minimum
- **Large text (≥ 18px)**: 3:1 minimum
- **UI components**: 3:1 minimum

### Color Testing
Test all color combinations with:
- [WebAIM Contrast Checker](https://webaim.org/resources/contrastchecker/)
- Browser DevTools (Lighthouse accessibility audit)

### Color Blindness Considerations
- Never rely on color alone to convey information
- Use icons, labels, or patterns in addition to color
- Test with color blindness simulators

## Dark Mode (Optional)

```css
@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
  --bg-default: var(--color-gray-900);
  --bg-surface: var(--color-gray-800);
  --text-default: var(--color-gray-100);
  --text-subtle: var(--color-gray-400);
  /* ... */
}
```

## Usage Examples

```css
/* Good */
.card {
  background: var(--bg-surface);
  color: var(--text-default);
  border: 1px solid var(--border-default);
}

/* Bad */
.card {
  background: #ffffff;
  color: #111827;
  border: 1px solid #d1d5db;
}
```

